        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:40PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 339 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Downtown Asheville, or near Bent Creek, moving north
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arden, Asheville, Woodfin, Biltmore Forest, Bent Creek, and Skyland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
